                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Last night in the dev chat someone asked why gates aa's cost so much.  Obviously the aa prices are still under nda but enough have leaked that they allowed the question.  The devs answered that it's because getting aa's is so much faster these days than even during early PoP.
<br />

<br />
On the surface that makes sense but the flaw in their philosophy is that the quality of the new aa's needs to increase proportionally to their cost.
<br />

<br />
Here's an analogy:
<br />

<br />
In the 80's a clunky VCR cost, say, $150, but it was badass at the time so people paid it and were happy.  Now say I make 20% more money than I did in the 80's.  VCR manufacturer's didn't increase the cost of VCR's by 20% because of that.  They came out with DVD players and charged 20% more for them instead.  
<br />

<br />
People will gladly pay 20% more than a VCR to get a DVD player bacause the difference is worth it.  SOE is trying to sell us the same clunky VCR's for 20% more than they did in past expansions.  There's no incentive to buy them over old aa's unless you own every VCR on the market and really need something to funnel your surplus income into.
<br />

<br />
I'd rather they charge 3-4x as much for aa's as they used to when earning 1 aa a night was nice, require you to have 100, 150 or even 250 aa's just to unlock them and then make them into DVD players so we have something to drive us to buy them.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
