                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Axterix EnObelix wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Dygar wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Charging more is fine. Not sure how you got that it wasn't from my analogy. There needs to be a greater reward for a greater cost. These rewards are less than or equal to the rewards for old aa's and cost significantly more. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
The thing is that the cost isn't the same as it used to be.  We've gotten much more effecient.  As a result, the cost of AAs is nothing.  And new AAs will reflect that.  A higher cost, so that the time they take is about equal to the time an AA ability would take back in the Luclin era.
<br />

<br />
Now, that means people will take older AAs first, most likely, bigger bang for the buck.  But otherwise, certain people would have the new AAs in the blink of an eye.
<br />

<br />
Personally, I wish they'd added 5 more levels and put these new AAs over those levels...and added code that without X number of AAs, you can't hit level X.  But they didn't add new levels.  Oh well, maybe next expansion.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I think what messed up the ratio was the LDoN experience.  You can gain about an aa an adventure with a good group.
<br />

<br />
However, as far as PoP zones are concerned, drop rates for better gear to make us more efficient and experience have been lowered in zones where there are more and more people now (e.g. Sol Ro Tower ornates).  Fire is still an excellent place to grab more XP, however the dev's are seeing more and more people able to grind in these zones.  I think the increase in cost was a business decision.  This next expansion has fewer AA's that cost more and no level advancement.  Fewer so they can maintain some aribtrary, pre-defined balance and higher cost so that most people won't max out their AA's before they can get another expansion out.  In addition, they have not increased the level cap so that we won't make the PoP zones trivial.  Keep in mind they are also adding yet another advancement system for leadership roles, and another point system in the form of a tribute system... and I think this further blurs the line of what constitutes as character advancement.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
