On hard.  On easy, it's about 1/2 of one.  And you can outdo that in PoP zones.  LDoN just provides a mix of gear acquisition, money, and xp in one package.  It has more people getting xp, but returns less xp per time period.  Especially when you factor in the downtime for your average group between missions.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">If the argument, that it is much easier go get AA these days and THEREFORE they want to charge more for the GoD AA skills holds true, then they should, consequently, reimburse ALL our AA points we spend so far and reset all our AA skills. Then they should raise the AA cost of ALL the skills to a level that seems fair with the current rate one acquires new points and we have to distribute our AA points again and buy the skills for the new, increased prize.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
